252
00:24:15,904 --> 00:24:17,839
...it destroyed ours.

253
00:24:17,839 --> 00:24:21,832
I was sent to a detention
home and lived at this woman's house.

254
00:24:23,011 --> 00:24:24,713
Mrs. Swerlin.

255
00:24:24,713 --> 00:24:28,150
Boys, this is Malcolm, our new guest.

256
00:24:28,150 --> 00:24:31,019
We'll treat him like a brother.

257
00:24:31,019 --> 00:24:34,756
I was special. The only
colored kid in the class.

258
00:24:34,756 --> 00:24:38,727
I became sort of a mascot,
like a pink poodle.

259
00:24:38,727 --> 00:24:42,564
I got called a nigger so much,
I didn't think it was wrong.

260
00:24:42,564 --> 00:24:45,433
I thought it was my name.

261
00:24:45,433 --> 00:24:48,770
They talked about me like I wasn't
there. Like a pedigreed dog...

262
00:24:48,770 --> 00:24:50,939
...or a horse.

263
00:24:50,939 --> 00:24:52,641
Like I was invisible.

264
00:24:52,641 --> 00:24:56,578
The important thing
is to be realistic.

265
00:24:56,578 --> 00:24:59,648
We all like you here, you know that.

266
00:24:59,648 --> 00:25:01,449
But you're a nigger...

267
00:25:01,449 --> 00:25:04,819
...and a lawyer is no realistic
goal for a nigger.

268
00:25:04,819 --> 00:25:07,722
But why, Mr. Ostrowski?

269
00:25:07,722 --> 00:25:10,192
I gets the best grades in class.

270
00:25:10,192 --> 00:25:13,895
I got voted class president.
I want to be a lawyer.

271
00:25:13,895 --> 00:25:17,632
I want you to think about
something that you can be.

272
00:25:17,632 --> 00:25:21,469
You're good with your hands,
making things.

273
00:25:21,469 --> 00:25:24,739
People would give you work. I would.

274
00:25:24,739 --> 00:25:27,209
Why not become a carpenter?

275
00:25:27,209 --> 00:25:30,946
That's a good profession for a colored.

276
00:25:30,946 --> 00:25:33,815
Wasn't your pa a carpenter?

277
00:25:33,815 --> 00:25:36,618
Jesus was a carpenter.

278
00:25:36,618 --> 00:25:40,611
People like you as a person.
You're doing real well.

279
00:25:41,690 --> 00:25:43,692
Remember what we said.

280
00:25:43,692 --> 00:25:46,494
"Nothing succeeds like success."
Say it.

281
00:25:46,494 --> 00:25:48,997
Nothing succeeds like success.

282
00:25:48,997 --> 00:25:51,099
As long as you're realistic.

283
00:25:51,099 --> 00:25:55,092
It's not the end of the world.

284
00:25:55,503 --> 00:25:58,273
I said, "Don't...

285
00:25:58,273 --> 00:26:01,243
...let them give that boy no pig."

286
00:26:01,243 --> 00:26:03,245
It wasn't the end
of the world for me.

287
00:26:03,245 --> 00:26:07,238
But it was the beginning of the end
for my mother.

288
00:26:10,852 --> 00:26:14,845
A right cross to the jaw by Louis.

289
00:26:16,024 --> 00:26:20,028
Louis takes Conn's head back
with a right uppercut.

290
00:26:20,028 --> 00:26:21,863
Louis hits left and right.

291
00:26:21,863 --> 00:26:25,667
And Conn is down
with a right cross to the jaw!

292
00:26:25,667 --> 00:26:27,302
He's taking the count.

293
00:26:27,302 --> 00:26:30,805
Four, five, six...

294
00:26:30,805 --> 00:26:34,175
...seven. He's on his back.
Eight. Nine.

295
00:26:34,175 --> 00:26:38,168
He's getting up!
The referee says it's all over!

296
00:26:41,716 --> 00:26:44,319
What in hell is going on?

297
00:26:44,319 --> 00:26:45,520
Nothing, Mr. Cooper.

298
00:26:45,520 --> 00:26:47,322
The customer's are hungry.

299
00:26:47,322 --> 00:26:49,057
Soup done finished, Mr. Cooper.

300
00:26:49,057 --> 00:26:51,326
Right, Mr. Charlie.

301
00:26:51,326 --> 00:26:53,561
The name is Mr. Cooper.

302
00:26:53,561 --> 00:26:55,297
Don't you forget it.

303
00:26:55,297 --> 00:26:59,290
Mr. Cooper.

304
00:27:00,302 --> 00:27:03,004
What's the matter with you?
You want me to get fired!

305
00:27:03,004 --> 00:27:04,572
I got a wife and six kids!

306
00:27:04,572 --> 00:27:07,075
Mr. Cooper is good white folk!

307
00:27:07,075 --> 00:27:11,068
You is a young fool!

308
00:27:18,053 --> 00:27:22,046
There'll never be another one like that!

309
00:27:22,123 --> 00:27:23,591
He's done it!

310
00:27:23,591 --> 00:27:26,061
And by a knockout...

311
00:27:26,061 --> 00:27:29,864
...and still the world's
heavyweight champion:

312
00:27:29,864 --> 00:27:32,167
Joe Louis!

313
00:27:32,167 --> 00:27:34,135
Ham and cheese!
Excuse me, sir.

314
00:27:34,135 --> 00:27:37,105
Ham and cheese here! I got coffee.

315
00:27:37,105 --> 00:27:40,041
- Lemon meringue pie.
- Hey, boy!

316
00:27:40,041 --> 00:27:43,645
- Ham and cheese.
- Yes, sir. Best in the house.

317
00:27:43,645 --> 00:27:46,614
- You're pleased with yourself.
- I aims to please, sir.

318
00:27:46,614 --> 00:27:47,916
I'm pleased to aim.

319
00:27:47,916 --> 00:27:51,909
- I like you, boy.
- Thank you.

320
00:27:53,588 --> 00:27:54,589
Keep the change.

321
00:27:54,589 --> 00:27:58,582
Right, sir!
Ham and cheese!

322
00:28:05,033 --> 00:28:09,026
Harlem!

323
00:28:27,789 --> 00:28:31,059
And here's Joe Lewis,
back in Harlem.

324
00:28:31,059 --> 00:28:33,328
They're celebrating!
They're going crazy!

325
00:28:33,328 --> 00:28:36,831
They're dancing! They're hanging
from street signs!

326
00:28:36,831 --> 00:28:38,933
Everybody's out!

327
00:28:38,933 --> 00:28:42,926
Everyone's having a great time!
Listen to them roar!

328
00:29:17,405 --> 00:29:20,675
Joe's a credit to his race.
What a fine gentleman!

329
00:29:20,675 --> 00:29:22,844
But he's also a fine American.

330
00:29:22,844 --> 00:29:26,837
The Brown Bomber, Joe Louis!

331
00:29:28,716 --> 00:29:30,118
Hey, sugar.

332
00:29:30,118 --> 00:29:33,021
- Slow down. What's your hurry?
- No hurry.

333
00:29:33,021 --> 00:29:35,790
Let me show you something new.

334
00:29:35,790 --> 00:29:38,026
I got gold watches, diamond rings.

335
00:29:38,026 --> 00:29:40,228
Any one of these. Whatever you need.

336
00:29:40,228 --> 00:29:41,362
I don't need that.

337
00:29:41,362 --> 00:29:44,732
You need something, baby.
Whatever you need!

338
00:29:44,732 --> 00:29:48,725
A couple of these
make a player look good.

339
00:30:17,832 --> 00:30:19,267
My man!

340
00:30:19,267 --> 00:30:23,260
- The word is "excuse me," boy.
- "Excuse me" don't shine my shoes.

341
00:30:23,805 --> 00:30:27,798
Then stay out of my way.

342
00:30:27,976 --> 00:30:31,969
Old country nigger.

343
00:30:34,215 --> 00:30:38,208
What you gonna do?

344
00:30:42,557 --> 00:30:46,550
Go home to your mama?

345
00:30:54,002 --> 00:30:57,995
Nigger, don't you ever in your life
say anything against my mother!

346
00:31:20,428 --> 00:31:24,421
Give me a whiskey.

347
00:31:31,005 --> 00:31:32,907
I ordered a single, Jack.

348
00:31:32,907 --> 00:31:36,900
The double's on that gentleman, "Jack."

349
00:31:40,081 --> 00:31:42,116
Who is that?

350
00:31:42,116 --> 00:31:44,586
That's West Indian Archie.

351
00:31:44,586 --> 00:31:47,488
What's his angle?

352
00:31:47,488 --> 00:31:51,481
Some of this, some of that.

353
00:32:03,137 --> 00:32:06,541
Nothing's gonna bite you.

354
00:32:06,541 --> 00:32:08,943
You look like you're new in town.

355
00:32:08,943 --> 00:32:12,213
From what I can see,
you're pretty handy with a bottle.

356
00:32:12,213 --> 00:32:14,549
He had it coming.

357
00:32:14,549 --> 00:32:18,542
Pull up a chair.

358
00:32:26,494 --> 00:32:28,363
What do they call you?

359
00:32:28,363 --> 00:32:30,331
Red.

360
00:32:30,331 --> 00:32:31,933
And I ain't no punk.

361
00:32:31,933 --> 00:32:34,002
You better not be.

362
00:32:34,002 --> 00:32:36,904
Any cat toe you down here,
you stand up or make tracks.

363
00:32:36,904 --> 00:32:38,272
Man live by his rep.

364
00:32:38,272 --> 00:32:40,575
Better believe it.

365
00:32:40,575 --> 00:32:42,310
So what do you do?

366
00:32:42,310 --> 00:32:45,113
Working on the train.

367
00:32:45,113 --> 00:32:46,347
Like that job?

368
00:32:46,347 --> 00:32:50,218
- Keeps me out of the Army.
- They want you, nothing'll keep you out.

369
00:32:50,218 --> 00:32:53,021
Not this boy.

370
00:32:53,021 --> 00:32:55,590
So I hear tell
you're a good man to know.

371
00:32:55,590 --> 00:32:57,959
- Where you hear that?
- Boston, where I'm from.

372
00:32:57,959 --> 00:32:59,694
Kiss my neck.

373
00:32:59,694 --> 00:33:01,496
I've never been in Beantown.

374
00:33:01,496 --> 00:33:05,366
Like the man said, a man's rep travels.

375
00:33:05,366 --> 00:33:09,003
How about that!

376
00:33:09,003 --> 00:33:10,304
You bullshitting me?

377
00:33:10,304 --> 00:33:13,508
My father told me
never bullshit a West Indian.

378
00:33:13,508 --> 00:33:15,009
Your daddy's West Indian?

379
00:33:15,009 --> 00:33:16,711
My mama.

380
00:33:16,711 --> 00:33:18,946
She's from Grenada.

381
00:33:18,946 --> 00:33:22,939
Grenada.

382
00:33:24,118 --> 00:33:25,353
I like this guy.

383
00:33:25,353 --> 00:33:28,122
I like your country.

384
00:33:28,122 --> 00:33:29,524
Grenada.

385
00:33:29,524 --> 00:33:32,460
Where'd you get them
goddamn vines you got on?

386
00:33:32,460 --> 00:33:34,362
And them shoes?

387
00:33:34,362 --> 00:33:35,363
Oh, my.

388
00:33:35,363 --> 00:33:37,065
We can do something about that.

389
00:33:37,065 --> 00:33:40,468
But he's putting a hurting
on my vision, man!

390
00:33:40,468 --> 00:33:42,336
Relax.

391
00:33:42,336 --> 00:33:43,538
How do I find you?

392
00:33:43,538 --> 00:33:45,540
You can't.

393
00:33:45,540 --> 00:33:47,175
I get ahold of you.

394
00:33:47,175 --> 00:33:49,477
All right, I'll write it down.

395
00:33:49,477 --> 00:33:51,512
Don't ever write anything down.

396
00:33:51,512 --> 00:33:53,548
File it up here.

397
00:33:53,548 --> 00:33:55,750
Like I do.

398
00:33:55,750 --> 00:33:59,721
If the man don't have any paper,
he will never have any proof.

399
00:33:59,721 --> 00:34:02,390
Dig?

400
00:34:02,390 --> 00:34:06,383
Yeah, I dig. Right.

401
00:34:10,031 --> 00:34:11,299
Look me in the face.

402
00:34:11,299 --> 00:34:15,292
Did you just con me?

403
00:34:15,770 --> 00:34:17,371
Yes, sir.

404
00:34:17,371 --> 00:34:18,439
Why?

405
00:34:18,439 --> 00:34:20,775
Because I want in.

406
00:34:20,775 --> 00:34:23,678
It don't take a lot to know
you're already there.

407
00:34:23,678 --> 00:34:25,580
At least he ain't lying.

408
00:34:25,580 --> 00:34:27,248
I have a run to make.

409
00:34:27,248 --> 00:34:31,241
Let me make that run
with you, Mr. Archie.

410
00:34:38,726 --> 00:34:40,795
I like your heart.

411
00:34:40,795 --> 00:34:43,464
I like your style.

412
00:34:43,464 --> 00:34:45,666
You might just do, Mr. Red.

413
00:34:45,666 --> 00:34:49,170
Unless you have to
get back to your train job.

414
00:34:49,170 --> 00:34:51,439
I've told him what to do
with that train.

415
00:34:51,439 --> 00:34:55,432
- When?
- Just now.

416
00:34:58,146 --> 00:35:00,114
All right.

417
00:35:00,114 --> 00:35:01,549
Come with me.

418
00:35:01,549 --> 00:35:05,119
I'm taking you shopping.

419
00:35:05,119 --> 00:35:07,488
Cadillac's the name.

420
00:35:07,488 --> 00:35:10,258
Sammy, man.

421
00:35:10,258 --> 00:35:14,251
- You ready?
- Good.

422
00:35:15,463 --> 00:35:19,456
Button more buttons on the jacket.

423
00:35:25,506 --> 00:35:27,842
You look good.

424
00:35:27,842 --> 00:35:29,410
But you're missing something.

425
00:35:29,410 --> 00:35:30,812
Frisk me.

426
00:35:30,812 --> 00:35:34,805
Go ahead, frisk me.

427
00:35:41,455 --> 00:35:45,448
Nothing, right?

428
00:35:48,796 --> 00:35:50,464
I'm still carrying.

429
00:35:50,464 --> 00:35:53,734
This was my first gun.

430
00:35:53,734 --> 00:35:57,727
Now it's yours.

431
00:36:02,476 --> 00:36:03,511
Thank you.

432
00:36:03,511 --> 00:36:05,613
You wear it...

433
00:36:05,613 --> 00:36:08,416
...wear it so.

434
00:36:08,416 --> 00:36:11,652
Small of the back.

435
00:36:11,652 --> 00:36:15,389
Now you're outfitted.

436
00:36:15,389 --> 00:36:16,757
Ready for the streets?

437
00:36:16,757 --> 00:36:18,893
I'm ready.

438
00:36:18,893 --> 00:36:20,127
Let them come.

439
00:36:20,127 --> 00:36:24,120
Let us now turn to
the Gospel According to St. John.

440
00:36:25,166 --> 00:36:26,567
Chapter 3...

441
00:36:26,567 --> 00:36:29,637
...verse 23.

442
00:36:29,637 --> 00:36:30,671
323.

443
00:36:30,671 --> 00:36:34,664
"And John also was baptizing
in Aenon near Salim...

444
00:36:37,111 --> 00:36:41,104
...because there was much water.

445
00:36:41,716 --> 00:36:45,319
And they came...

446
00:36:45,319 --> 00:36:49,312
...and were baptized."

447
00:36:49,757 --> 00:36:53,261
313.

448
00:36:53,261 --> 00:36:54,629
255.

449
00:36:54,629 --> 00:36:57,131
It got to be 251.

450
00:36:57,131 --> 00:36:58,165
403.

451
00:36:58,165 --> 00:37:00,268
I saw it in my dream.

452
00:37:00,268 --> 00:37:02,803
555.

453
00:37:02,803 --> 00:37:06,474
- What do you know?
- I feel straight.

454
00:37:06,474 --> 00:37:07,875
Your lucky day.

455
00:37:07,875 --> 00:37:10,745
Roll it for me.

456
00:37:10,745 --> 00:37:13,514
I told you, no paper, no trouble.

457
00:37:13,514 --> 00:37:15,950
I'm working on it.

458
00:37:15,950 --> 00:37:18,619
I keep my numbers in my head.

459
00:37:18,619 --> 00:37:22,612
I've never written a number down yet.
Remember that.

460
00:37:37,471 --> 00:37:41,464
Your turn.

461
00:37:44,946 --> 00:37:48,939
Easy.

462
00:37:49,717 --> 00:37:52,920
Easy.

463
00:37:52,920 --> 00:37:53,921
You there?

464
00:37:53,921 --> 00:37:55,523
If I ain't, I'm next door.

465
00:37:55,523 --> 00:37:59,516
Nothing in this world can give you
that real deep cool.

466
00:37:59,894 --> 00:38:03,887
The girl.

467
00:38:18,379 --> 00:38:22,372
About as mellow as I can be.

468
00:38:25,820 --> 00:38:27,254
Cool enough to kill.

469
00:38:27,254 --> 00:38:31,258
I realize that.

470
00:38:31,258 --> 00:38:35,251
- Easy, easy, easy, easy.
- Stick them up.

471
00:38:37,398 --> 00:38:40,935
Archie!

472
00:38:40,935 --> 00:38:44,928
Baby?

473
00:38:47,875 --> 00:38:51,868
Malcolm, you're so funny.

474
00:38:52,413 --> 00:38:56,406
Give me some money, baby.

475
00:38:59,453 --> 00:39:01,389
Come on, baby.

476
00:39:01,389 --> 00:39:05,382
The bitch move too slow.

477
00:39:07,028 --> 00:39:10,598
Sometimes this guy
has a big ugly mouth.

478
00:39:10,598 --> 00:39:13,267
What time is it, baby?

479
00:39:13,267 --> 00:39:15,469
8:21.

480
00:39:15,469 --> 00:39:17,505
I like that. Combinate me.

481
00:39:17,505 --> 00:39:19,407
821.

482
00:39:19,407 --> 00:39:22,343
128.

483
00:39:22,343 --> 00:39:24,011
218.

484
00:39:24,011 --> 00:39:28,004
I'm taking the bet.

485
00:39:29,817 --> 00:39:33,810
Time to reload.

486
00:40:19,133 --> 00:40:22,536
I thought you said we was going
to the movies last night.

487
00:40:22,536 --> 00:40:23,671
You said that.

488
00:40:23,671 --> 00:40:25,806
I'm sorry. I say a lot of things.

489
00:40:25,806 --> 00:40:26,874
I believed you.

490
00:40:26,874 --> 00:40:30,867
Do your job now. Get me a pack
of Lucky Strikes and a cognac.

491
00:40:43,657 --> 00:40:44,959
Daniel come in yet?

492
00:40:44,959 --> 00:40:47,361
Ain't that him?

493
00:40:47,361 --> 00:40:48,896
Gorgeous!

494
00:40:48,896 --> 00:40:52,889
How you been today?
You been waiting long?

495
00:40:53,667 --> 00:40:57,071
Let me look at you.

496
00:40:57,071 --> 00:41:00,808
- I've been missing you today, Laura.
- How you doing, baby?

497
00:41:00,808 --> 00:41:04,712
I'm all right. Copacetic. Great.
Did you work today?

498
00:41:04,712 --> 00:41:07,515
No, baby, I didn't go to work.

499
00:41:07,515 --> 00:41:10,885
- I need a five-spot.
- I gave you 10 this morning.

500
00:41:10,885 --> 00:41:13,554
Give me the goddamn $5!

501
00:41:13,554 --> 00:41:15,189
It ain't the money.
I wanna...

502
00:41:15,189 --> 00:41:17,024
...make sure you're okay.

503
00:41:17,024 --> 00:41:19,927
I gotta pay back this guy.

504
00:41:19,927 --> 00:41:22,563
I'll be right back.

505
00:41:22,563 --> 00:41:24,064
Like last time?

506
00:41:24,064 --> 00:41:26,400
I swear, I'll be right back.

507
00:41:26,400 --> 00:41:30,393
Laura, I love you.

508
00:41:36,844 --> 00:41:40,514
You know that chick?

509
00:41:40,514 --> 00:41:42,583
You a private detective now?

510
00:41:42,583 --> 00:41:43,717
Just asking.

511
00:41:43,717 --> 00:41:45,953
Don't ask me no goddamn questions.

512
00:41:45,953 --> 00:41:49,590
I ask you the questions.
You understand?

513
00:41:49,590 --> 00:41:52,092
- She come in here a lot?
- Almost every night.

514
00:41:52,092 --> 00:41:54,828
With him?

515
00:41:54,828 --> 00:41:58,821
- She know he's high?
- Lf she got eyes, she do.

516
00:41:59,600 --> 00:42:00,935
She ain't hooking?

517
00:42:00,935 --> 00:42:03,437
Not yet, Red.

518
00:42:03,437 --> 00:42:07,430
But the way things are,
he'll turn her out any day now.

519
00:42:11,579 --> 00:42:13,113
You stuck on her?

520
00:42:13,113 --> 00:42:17,106
That's your problem.
You need to mind your own business.

521
00:42:19,954 --> 00:42:21,188
Don't do that!

522
00:42:21,188 --> 00:42:25,181
I wanna talk to you, all right?
Have a seat.

523
00:42:33,133 --> 00:42:35,669
- Don't pay him any mind, hear?
- All right.

524
00:42:35,669 --> 00:42:39,662
- All right?
- I'm all right.

525
00:42:43,944 --> 00:42:47,937
Buy yourself something nice.

526
00:42:57,858 --> 00:43:01,851
Hey, baby.

527
00:43:04,298 --> 00:43:08,291
Give me a light.

528
00:43:16,310 --> 00:43:18,812
You look uptight.
What's the problem?

529
00:43:18,812 --> 00:43:19,980
- No problem.
- Sure?

530
00:43:19,980 --> 00:43:23,973
Everything's all right.
I'm not worrying about it.

531
00:43:25,653 --> 00:43:27,921
I'm thinking about my money.

532
00:43:27,921 --> 00:43:29,923
Six big ones you owe me, right?

533
00:43:29,923 --> 00:43:30,958
What?

534
00:43:30,958 --> 00:43:32,226
821.
It hit, didn't it?

535
00:43:32,226 --> 00:43:34,261
You didn't have 821.

536
00:43:34,261 --> 00:43:38,132
Were you high? I threw the slats
at you, told you to combinate me.

537
00:43:38,132 --> 00:43:39,667
You never had it.

538
00:43:39,667 --> 00:43:42,269
I tell you I did. Sophia was there.

539
00:43:42,269 --> 00:43:44,071
You remember, don't you?

540
00:43:44,071 --> 00:43:46,674
What would she say?

541
00:43:46,674 --> 00:43:48,342
Don't do this.

542
00:43:48,342 --> 00:43:49,843
All right?

543
00:43:49,843 --> 00:43:53,080
All right.

544
00:43:53,080 --> 00:43:55,082
All right, skip it.

545
00:43:55,082 --> 00:43:57,351
But you're slipping, aren't you?

546
00:43:57,351 --> 00:44:01,344
You done slipped.

547
00:44:02,690 --> 00:44:06,683
Archie, wait.

548
00:44:15,369 --> 00:44:18,305
Come on, Archie. Look...

549
00:44:18,305 --> 00:44:21,375
Come on. You want a drink
