551
00:44:25,245 --> 00:44:29,238
All right?

552
00:44:30,718 --> 00:44:33,320
Come, Sam.

553
00:44:33,320 --> 00:44:37,313
I'll be right there, man.

554
00:44:41,829 --> 00:44:44,131
Twenty-two years.

555
00:44:44,131 --> 00:44:48,001
Twenty-two years, I never
knowed him to forget a number.

556
00:44:48,001 --> 00:44:49,737
First time for everything.

557
00:44:49,737 --> 00:44:51,772
What are you talking about?

558
00:44:51,772 --> 00:44:55,765
The first thing he'll do is check
with the collector for an oversight.

559
00:44:56,643 --> 00:45:00,647
His rep is on the line. So is yours.

560
00:45:00,647 --> 00:45:04,640
And, Red, if you're lying,
you're a dead man.

561
00:45:05,285 --> 00:45:09,278
Dead, dead, dead.

562
00:45:10,724 --> 00:45:14,717
You go and tell him that.

563
00:45:19,299 --> 00:45:22,002
My man, Red.

564
00:45:22,002 --> 00:45:24,371
Night to you.

565
00:45:24,371 --> 00:45:28,364
I don't understand Archie.
You had the number.

566
00:46:01,408 --> 00:46:05,401
Didn't I tell you never sit
with your back to no door?

567
00:46:10,150 --> 00:46:13,353
You know what?

568
00:46:13,353 --> 00:46:15,355
You're a damn liar.

569
00:46:15,355 --> 00:46:19,348
And so is she.

570
00:46:20,294 --> 00:46:22,129
So you figure to take me...

571
00:46:22,129 --> 00:46:24,498
...you bastard?

572
00:46:24,498 --> 00:46:26,066
I'm taking you.

573
00:46:26,066 --> 00:46:28,502
- So it's you and me?
- That's right.

574
00:46:28,502 --> 00:46:30,337
I'll give you the $600.

575
00:46:30,337 --> 00:46:32,306
- I don't want it.
- I'm wearing.

576
00:46:32,306 --> 00:46:36,299
There's three guns on you,
so you take your chances.

577
00:46:47,054 --> 00:46:51,047
Let's walk.

578
00:46:56,163 --> 00:46:59,266
So this is how I'm going out?

579
00:46:59,266 --> 00:47:02,936
- In a toe-down?
- Toe-down, yes.

580
00:47:02,936 --> 00:47:06,929
- Let's go.
- We'll let Billie finish.

581
00:47:51,818 --> 00:47:53,287
Thank you.

582
00:47:53,287 --> 00:47:57,280
Thank you very much. Thank you.

583
00:48:18,812 --> 00:48:21,048
Wake up.

584
00:48:21,048 --> 00:48:24,351
Wake up!

585
00:48:24,351 --> 00:48:28,344
There's somebody out there.

586
00:48:29,122 --> 00:48:33,115
Wake the kids.

587
00:48:44,571 --> 00:48:48,564
Follow me! Wait! Wait!

588
00:48:50,110 --> 00:48:54,103
Go! Go!

589
00:48:54,281 --> 00:48:58,274
Careful!

590
00:48:58,986 --> 00:49:02,623
- Good thing we're all good Christians.
- It's time for you to leave this town.

591
00:49:02,623 --> 00:49:04,091
It's a free country.

592
00:49:04,091 --> 00:49:07,661
We warned you about Garvey preaching!
Stirring up the good niggras!

593
00:49:07,661 --> 00:49:09,029
I ain't a boy!

594
00:49:09,029 --> 00:49:10,897
- I'm a man!
- You're a dead nigger.

595
00:49:10,897 --> 00:49:13,667
And a real man don't hide
behind sheets!

596
00:49:13,667 --> 00:49:17,660
You take these bullets for them sheets!

597
00:49:22,876 --> 00:49:25,512
I know you're a better shot than that.

598
00:49:25,512 --> 00:49:27,614
You should've killed them.

599
00:49:27,614 --> 00:49:29,916
You should've shot them all dead.

600
00:49:29,916 --> 00:49:32,419
I just wanted to scare them.

601
00:49:32,419 --> 00:49:36,412
They won't be around here
bothering us no more.

602
00:49:36,523 --> 00:49:39,359
They won't be here no time soon.

603
00:49:39,359 --> 00:49:42,929
I'm a man!

604
00:49:42,929 --> 00:49:46,922
That'll teach you.

605
00:49:51,471 --> 00:49:52,472
Get a doctor!

606
00:49:52,472 --> 00:49:56,209
He doesn't need a doctor,
he needs a preacher.


